 Research</a></i>. <b>51</b> (1): 5\u201318. <a href=\"/wiki/Digital_object_identifier\" title=\"Digital object identifier\">doi</a>:<a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"//doi.org/10.1177/0022343313507302\">10.1177/0022343313507302</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Journal+of+Peace+Research&amp;rft.atitle=Early+warning+signals+for+war+in+the+news&amp;rft.volume=51&amp;rft.issue=1&amp;rft.pages=5-18&amp;rft.date=2014-01&amp;rft_id=info%3Adoi%2F10.1177%2F0022343313507302&amp;rft.aulast=Chadefaux&amp;rft.aufirst=Thomas&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.researchgate.net%2Fprofile%2FThomas_Chadefaux%2Fpublication%2F256044330_Early_Warning_Signals_for_War_in_the_News%2Flinks%2F0c96052a992664d50d000000.pdf&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AConflict+early+warning\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-6\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-6\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite id=\"CITEREFO&#39;Brien2010\" class=\"citation journal\">O'Brien, Sean P. (March 2010). \"Crisis early warning and decision support: contemporary approaches and thoughts on future research\". <i><a href=\"/wiki/International_Studies_Review\" title=\"International Studies Review\">International Studies Review</a></i>. <b>12</b> (1): 87\u2013104. <a href=\"/wiki/Digital_object_identifier\" title=\"Digital object identifier\">doi</a>:<a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"//doi.org/10.1111/j.1468-2486.2009.00914.x\">10.1111/j.1468-2486.2009.00914.x</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=International+Studies+Review&amp;rft.atitle=Crisis+early+warning+and+decision+support%3A+contemporary+approaches+and+thoughts+on+future+research&amp;rft.volume=12&amp;rft.issue=1&amp;rft.pages=87-104&amp;rft.date=2010-03&amp;rft_id=info%3Adoi%2F10.1111%2Fj.1468-2486.2009.00914.x&amp;rft.aulast=O%27Brien&amp;rft.aufirst=Sean+P.&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AConflict+early+warning\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-FAST-7\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">^ <a href=\"#cite_ref-FAST_7-0\"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-FAST_7-1\"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite id=\"CITEREFKrummenacher2006\" class=\"citation book\">Krummenacher, Heinz (2006). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://books.google.com/books?id=o6Fv7XFhQgMC&amp;pg=PA71\">\"Computer assisted early warning\u2014the FAST example\"</a>.  In <a href=\"/wiki/Robert_Trappl\" title=\"Robert Trappl\">Trappl, Robert</a>. <i>Programming for peace: computer-aided methods for international conflict resolution and prevention</i>. Advances in group decision and negotiation. <b>2</b>. Dordrecht: <a href=\"/wiki/Springer_Verlag\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Springer Verlag\">Springer Verlag</a>. pp.&#160;71\u201380. <a href=\"/wiki/Digital_object_identifier\" title=\"Digital object identifier\">doi</a>:<a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"//doi.org/10.1007/1-4020-4390-2_4\">10.1007/1-4020-4390-2_4</a>. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/1402043775\" title=\"Special:BookSources/1402043775\">1402043775</a>. <a href=\"/wiki/OCLC\" title=\"OCLC\">OCLC</a>&#160;<a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"//www.worldcat.org/oclc/63764074\">63764074</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.atitle=Computer+assisted+early+warning%E2%80%94the+FAST+example&amp;rft.btitle=Programming+for+peace%3A+computer-aided+methods+for+international+confl